rritory’, <i>walah</i> ‘stranger’, or <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. Medieval forms can be found to support all these theories, and it is possible that several names have fallen together, or that the name was subjected to reanalysis by folk etymology at an early date."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":7,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Geoffrey Loveday was born about 1308, in Berkshire, England. He married Mrs Geoffrey Loveday before 1326, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1326, in England, at the age of 19."},"et":{"circa 1308–1326":"umbes 1308–1326","–Female":"Surnud","1326–1352":"1326–1352","1308–1326":"1308–1326","before 1326":"enne 1326","1326":"1326","1315":"1315","circa 1308":"umbes 1308","1352":"1352","1308":"1308","1317":"1317","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England","Shrivenham, Berkshire, England":"Shrivenham, Berkshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"circa 1308–1326":"noin 1308–1326","–Female":"Kuollut","1326–1352":"1326–1352","1308–1326":"1308–1326","before 1326":"ennen vuotta 1326","1326":"1326","1315":"1315","circa 1308":"noin 1308","1352":"1352","1308":"1308","1317":"1317","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England","Shrivenham, Berkshire, England":"Shrivenham, Berkshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"circa 1308–1326":"environ 1308–1326","–Female":"Décédée","1326–1352":"1326–1352","1308–1326":"1308–1326","before 1326":"avant 1326","1326":"1326","1315":"1315","circa 1308":"environ 1308","1352":"1352","1308":"1308","1317":"1317","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Angleterre","Shrivenham, Berkshire, England":"Shrivenham, Berkshire, Angleterre","England":"A